00:05.105 --> 00:06.338
¶ and you'll hear a tale ¶

00:06.407 --> 00:08.640
¶ a tale of a fateful trip ¶

00:08.708 --> 00:11.276
¶ that started
from this tropic port ¶

00:11.344 --> 00:13.011
¶ aboard this tiny ship ¶

00:13.080 --> 00:15.948
¶ the mate was a mighty
sailin' man ¶

00:16.017 --> 00:17.683
¶ the skipper
brave and sure ¶

00:17.751 --> 00:20.318
¶ 5 passengers
set sail that day ¶

00:20.387 --> 00:23.121
¶ for a 3-hour tour ¶

00:23.190 --> 00:25.457
¶ a 3-hour tour ¶

00:25.525 --> 00:27.592
[thunder]

00:27.661 --> 00:29.561
¶ The weather
started getting rough ¶

00:29.630 --> 00:31.796
¶ the tiny ship was tossed ¶

00:31.865 --> 00:34.600
¶ if not for the courage
of the fearless crew ¶

00:34.668 --> 00:37.135
¶ the <i> minnow</i>
would be lost ¶

00:37.204 --> 00:39.337
¶ the <i> minnow</i>
would be lost ¶

00:39.406 --> 00:40.939
¶ the ship set ground
on the shore ¶

00:41.008 --> 00:43.775
¶ of this uncharted
desert isle ¶

00:43.844 --> 00:46.144
¶ with gilligan ¶

00:46.213 --> 00:48.312
¶ the skipper, too ¶

00:48.381 --> 00:50.248
¶ the millionaire ¶

00:50.316 --> 00:52.851
¶ and his wife ¶

00:52.920 --> 00:55.821
¶ the movie star ¶

00:55.889 --> 00:57.455
¶ and the rest ¶

00:57.524 --> 01:02.594
¶ are here
on gilligan's isle ¶

